Strict Rules:
1. Currency & Math: ALWAYS use the `rust_decimal` crate for financial calculations. Never use f32/f64 floats.
2. Axum 0.8 Syntax: `Router::with_state` must be applied at the top level in `main.rs`, NOT inside nested router builder functions. `Router<AppState>` cannot be passed to `serve`.
3. Error Handling: Use `thiserror = "2.0"`. Never use `?` on raw `sqlx::Error` when checking for `RowNotFound`; use explicit match arms to map to domain errors (e.g., `InventoryError::SkuNotFound`).
4. Database Enums: Always map `sqlx` enums using `#[sqlx(rename_all = "snake_case")]` to match PostgreSQL labels.
5. Database Queries: Prefer `sqlx::query_as` with `.bind()` during rapid development to avoid compile-time DB locks.
6. Business Logic: Do not put business logic (like NYS Tax or Employee Pricing) inside API route handlers. Handlers only parse requests and return JSON. Logic lives in `server/src/logic/` and `server/src/services/`.
7. UX Alignment Surface Modes: Treat `register` and `customers` as `POS-Core`; all other workspaces are `BackOffice`. New UX changes must preserve this mode intent (speed-first vs clarity-first).
8. UI Primitives First: Prefer shared tokens/primitives over one-off styles. Reuse `density-compact`, `density-standard`, `ui-card`, `ui-input`, `ui-btn-primary`, `ui-btn-secondary`, and `ui-pill` before introducing custom control variants.
9. Financial Action Safety (QBO): For QBO approve/sync/finalize flows, use explicit confirmation UX and preserve access-log behavior for write actions (`qbo_mapping_save`, `qbo_granular_mapping_save`, `qbo_staging_approve`, `qbo_sync_success`, `qbo_sync_failed`).
10. Ledger Signal Integrity: `gift_card` splits must carry valid `sub_type` (`paid_liability` or `loyalty_giveaway`); reject `sub_type` on non-gift-card methods. `applied_deposit_amount` must be non-negative and must not exceed its split amount.
11. QA Baseline Requirement for UX/Financial Flows: For significant POS/QBO workflow changes, update/verify Playwright coverage under `client/e2e/` and refresh snapshots when UI materially changes.
12. E2E Base URL in this repo: Prefer `E2E_BASE_URL=http://localhost:5173` for Playwright runs (localhost is reliable in this environment; 127.0.0.1 may fail browser connection). For full-suite stability use `npx playwright test --workers=1` from `client/` (see docs/ROS_UI_CONSISTENCY_PLAN.md Phase 5).
